{"absolute_url":"https://boards.greenhouse.io/canonical/jobs/4605464","data_compliance":[{"type":"gdpr","requires_consent":false,"requires_processing_consent":false,"requires_retention_consent":false,"retention_period":null}],"education":"education_required","internal_job_id":1875080,"location":{"name":"Office Based - Taipei, Taiwan"},"metadata":[{"id":186225,"name":"People management responsibilities?","value":true,"value_type":"yes_no"},{"id":149021,"name":"Employment Length","value":"Full-time","value_type":"single_select"},{"id":675557,"name":"Core skills","value":["Analysers","Competitor","Developer","Doer","Generalist","Helper","Leader","Manager","Organiser","Planner","Problem Solver","Technologist"],"value_type":"multi_select"},{"id":2739136,"name":"External Departments (website)","value":["Engineering"],"value_type":"multi_select"},{"id":2739137,"name":"One line job description","value":"Lead a team to bring high-quality Ubuntu certified devices directly to millions of users with our world-leading partners.","value_type":"long_text"},{"id":3209541,"name":"Canonical site","value":[],"value_type":"multi_select"},{"id":3587161,"name":"LinkedIn Posting Level","value":"Mid-Senior","value_type":"single_select"},{"id":11961371,"name":"Featured job (Talent Team to complete)","value":null,"value_type":"yes_no"}],"id":4605464,"updated_at":"2023-11-08T02:45:26-05:00","requisition_id":"745","title":"Ubuntu Enablement - Software Engineering Manager","pay_input_ranges":[],"content":"Canonical's Device Delivery Team works with tier-1 OEM and ODM customers to pre-load Ubuntu Desktop and Ubuntu Core, bringing Ubuntu directly to millions of users.\nAs a ​Software Engineering Manager​ you will lead and manage the software engineering team to deliver OEM enablement projects. This fast-paced environment requires excellent time management, deep knowledge of the Linux system​, low-level debugging, critical thinking, problem-solving skills and management ability.\nKey responsibilities\n\nRecruit, motivate, mentor, and enable your team to succeed in delivering quality products\nSet goals with the team; prioritize tasks, identify and measure team health indicators\nMaximise the results of team members and support their career growth\nCoordinate with project managers, HWE, QA and certification management\nMonitor projects from kickoff to post-mortem and handle escalations\nCommunicate, understand, and resolve the technical challenge with OEMs, ODMs, SiPs, IHVs\nPrioritize customer requests globally\nCollaborate with product engineering teams (including Desktop, Foundations, Kernel, and Security)\nProvide leadership for methodologies, strategies, standards, tools, and best practices\nMust be able to travel to the EU, USA, China, and Taiwan; (after covid-19 restrictions lift)\n\nRequired skills and experience\n\nA Bachelor (or higher) degree in STEM, preferably computer science or software engineering\nProven track record in technical roles with Linux, preferably Ubuntu or Debian\nCommitment to development and testing methodologies, and maintainable code quality\nExperience with management responsibilities\nAbility to work collaboratively in a team environment\nAbility to be productive in a globally distributed team through self-discipline and self-motivation\nCommitment and energy to deliver on schedule\nStrong English and Chinese language communication skills, both written and verbal\n\nDesirable skills and experience\n\nMaking technical decisions for a team as a tech lead\nSoftware architecture and design experience\nSoftware development or operations experience with: Ubuntu - kernel and userspace, deb/snap packaging, QEMU/KVM, LXC/LXD, Containers, Python, Go, C, bash, Postgresql, Mongo, Kubernetes, OpenStack, Ceph, AI/ML\nParticipation in open-source development projects\nExperience with CI/CD\n\nCanonical is an equal opportunity employer\nCanonical believes a diverse workforce enhances our ability to deliver world class software and services which meet the world’s computing needs. We are committed to ensuring equal employment opportunities to all qualified individuals. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, disability, age, or veteran status.\n#LI-ET1 #stack","departments":[{"id":85345,"name":"Engineering","child_ids":[],"parent_id":null}],"offices":[{"id":44176,"name":"Office Based - Taipei, Taiwan","location":"Taipei City, Taiwan","child_ids":[],"parent_id":73278}],"compliance":null,"demographic_questions":null,"questions":[{"description":null,"label":"First Name","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"first_name","type":"input_text","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Last Name","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"last_name","type":"input_text","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Email","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"email","type":"input_text","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Phone","required":false,"fields":[{"name":"phone","type":"input_text","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Resume/CV","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"resume","type":"input_file","values":[]},{"name":"resume_text","type":"textarea","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Cover Letter","required":false,"fields":[{"name":"cover_letter","type":"input_file","values":[]},{"name":"cover_letter_text","type":"textarea","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Describe your professional software engineering leadership experience","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"question_36165241","type":"textarea","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"Describe your low-level firmware, BIOS, boot loader and Linux kernel experience","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"question_36165242","type":"textarea","values":[]}]},{"description":null,"label":"What time zone are you in?","required":true,"fields":[{"name":"question_36165243","type":"multi_value_single_